# Dashboard UI Rules

Dashboard UI must feel:
- modern
- clean
- operational
- scalable
- lightweight
- mobile-first
- professional
- high-end
- minimalist

Frontend stack:
- Blade
- TailwindCSS
- DaisyUI or Flowbite
- Alpine.js

Use DaisyUI as the default component layer unless a module explicitly needs a custom primitive.
Use theme-style.json as the source for radius, accent, and shadow values.
No external CDNs; all assets must be bundled locally.

Always:
- build reusable Blade components
- centralize layouts
- centralize tables/forms/modals
- use consistent spacing and typography
- support responsive behavior
- avoid layout shift by reserving space for loading and empty states

Avoid:
- duplicated UI structures
- inconsistent layouts
- patch-style fixes
- hardcoded repeated markup
- random colors/styles

Dashboard should include:
- sidebar
- navbar
- stat cards
- tables
- filters
- action dropdowns
- loading states
- empty states
- confirmation dialogs

Think in:
Dashboard System → Module → Reusable Components
